## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript
- Prisma 5 + PostgreSQL (Supabase)
- NextAuth for auth; Tailwind CSS for styling

## Secrets
- **Never** put real API keys, client secrets, passwords, or NEXTAUTH_SECRET in any file that is committed (no .md, .ts, .tsx, .env.example, or docs). Use placeholders only (e.g. `your-google-client-id`, `your-nextauth-secret`). Real credentials belong only in local `.env` (already in .gitignore).

## Conventions
- Prefer server components; use "use client" only when needed (state, events, browser APIs).
- Data: domain types in src/domain, server/db in src/server, UI in src/ui.
- Use existing components (Card, Section, etc.); match F1 theme (red accents, dark bg, circuit motifs).
- Supabase: DATABASE_URL must include ?sslmode=require for Prisma CLI and runtime.

## Output
- Prefer small, targeted edits. Preserve existing patterns and file structure unless the task requires otherwise.
